                            <container4_copy_copy_1601311836
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <separator
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756456518]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2022-12-06T18:24:11.753-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2022-12-06T18:24:11.753-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-04-18T10:43:54.118-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Making sustainable choices"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2022-12-06T18:36:22.490-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>In Singapore, two employees with a passion for environmental sustainability saw the open call for new ideas and began brainstorming.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Together, Niki Wong, principal research scientist, and Gauri Salunkhe, operations engineer, identified a way to recycle waste at their facility, which manufactures biologics and relies on the industry standard approach of using several single-use plastics in the process.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Currently these plastics, which include items like bottles, sterile bags and connected tubing, are safely disposed of after each use. Some recycling methods are available, but they require the plastics to be separated and thoroughly cleaned and sanitized beforehand, which is resource-intensive.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“We saw an opportunity to find a novel method to recycle these mixed plastics and result in a 20% increase in our facility’s recycling rate,” Salunkhe says.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>As a challenge winner, the team is now evaluating vendors that can take the plastics and solve some of the sorting and cleaning challenges. In turn, this approach would help accelerate AbbVie’s global target of achieving a 50% combined recycling rate for both hazardous and non-hazardous waste by 2025.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“This challenge is really about raising awareness and encouraging people to make more sustainable choices,” she says.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <text_354147214_copy_
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2022-12-05T16:14:00.148-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="schafsm"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-29T16:07:42.000-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
